25 LC 44 2907
House Resolution 11
By: Representative Davis of the 87th
A RESOLUTION
1 Urging the Georgia Environmental Protection Division, the Environmental Protection
2 Agency, and the DeKalb County government to resolve sewage pollution and spills; and for
3 other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, sewage pollution and spills have been a persistent issue in various areas of
5 DeKalb County, disproportionately affecting predominantly Black "nonpriority" areas; and
6 WHEREAS, the health and well-being of residents in these areas are compromised due to
7 the adverse effects of sewage pollution on the environment and public health; and
8 WHEREAS, it is essential to address these issues promptly and ensure that all residents of
9 DeKalb County have access to clean and safe environments; and
10 WHEREAS, there is a disparity between the prioritization of areas in DeKalb County, with
11 North DeKalb receiving preferential treatment over South DeKalb.
12 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
13 the members of this body urge the Georgia Environmental Protection Division, the
14 Environmental Protection Agency, and the DeKalb County government to take immediate
H. R. 11
