15 and comprehensive actions to fix and eliminate sewage pollution and spills in predominantly
16 Black "nonpriority" areas of DeKalb County.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body urge the Georgia
18 Environmental Protection Division, the Environmental Protection Agency, and the DeKalb
19 County government to establish a date certain within a consent decree for the resolution of
20 sewage pollution and spills in these areas, prioritizing the protection of the environment and
21 the health of residents.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body encourage the Georgia
23 Environmental Protection Division, the Environmental Protection Agency, and the DeKalb
24 County government to treat South DeKalb with the same level of priority as North DeKalb
25 in addressing sewage pollution and spills, ensuring that equitable resources and efforts are
26 allocated to both regions.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
28 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to
29 officials of the Georgia Environmental Protection Division, the Environmental Protection
30 Agency, and the DeKalb County government.
